--  v4.7.3 [PREVIOUS BUILD]
--    Fix:   Phase 2 shaped-brick builder: face-attach anchor size
--           now uses anchorMeta.targetSize instead of anchorPart.Size
--           for the faceCenter calculation. anchorPart.Size is the
--           server-replicated value and can lag by one frame when the
--           anchor was just shaped in the previous iteration, producing
--           a wrong face-center and placing the new brick at the wrong
--           position. targetSize is always authoritative and never stale.
--    Fix:   Phase 2 shaped-brick builder: after lastBuilt fires via
--           ChildAdded, wait SHAPE_WAIT before reading part.Size so the
--           server's inherited size (copied from the anchor via face-
--           attach) has time to replicate. Then skip applyShapeOps
--           entirely when the inherited size already matches the target
--           within 0.49 studs on every axis. Previously, reading the
--           stale 4×4×4 default caused the full reshape to fire on every
--           wall brick (e.g. 4,1,4 → 4,4,2 repeated for the entire wall)
--           even though the anchor was already the correct size and the
--           server would have spawned the brick at 4,4,2. The skip is
--           logged as "Size already correct — shaping skipped."
--    New:   Phase 2 pass E — two-tier shape fix system:
--           Tier 1 (ROLLING, woven into D loop): every 10 bricks placed,
--           re-verify the last 10 builtPart entries immediately while
--           still mid-build. Mismatched bricks are teleported to and
--           re-shaped shrink-first. Missing bricks are recovered via
--           face-attach off the nearest live placed brick, settled
--           (SHAPE_WAIT), then shaped to target. Logged as ROLL@N.
--           Catches dropouts before downstream bricks chain off a broken
--           anchor, preventing cascade failures in dense shaped grids.
--           Tier 2 (FULL SWEEPS, after D loop): up to 5 convergence
--           sweeps over all N shaped bricks. Size mismatch → teleport +
--           shrink-first applyShapeOps. Missing → face-attach recovery
--           via shared rebuildMissingBrick() (uses bestFace dot-product
--           selection, ChildAdded watcher rebuildConn). Stops early once
--           a full sweep produces zero fixes or recoveries.
--    Fix:   Face-attach (buildEv on a BasePart anchor) is infinite-range
--           — the server's brick-to-brick build path has no proximity
--           check. Removed all teleport+Anchored sequences that preceded
--           face-attach FireServer calls (rolling-check recovery and
--           rebuildMissingBrick). Teleports are kept exclusively for
--           Shape remote calls (applyShapeOps callers), which ARE
--           range-checked server-side. Each recovery now teleports only
--           AFTER the new brick arrives, right before applyShapeOps.
--           Strategy B/C terrain builds keep their teleports (Terrain
--           builds ARE range-checked). Strategy A was already clean.
--    New:   Debug → BlitzBuild Speed Test redesigned: schedule now starts
--           at 20 bps and steps +3 per cube (20, 23, 26…47) instead of
--           the old 2→20 bps warm-up. Tracks wall-clock time per cube
