-- ── DEV RULES (READ BEFORE TOUCHING ANYTHING) ────────────────
--  1. CRLF line endings       → LF only (Unix). CRLF will crash on load.
--  2. += operators            → not valid Lua; always write x = x + 1
--  3. goto / ::labels::       → unsupported; use break + flag variables
--  4. OverlapParams.new()     → always wrap in pcall(); can error on old exec
--  5. Bare filesystem calls   → guard with: if typeof(fn)=="function" then
--  6. NO UICorner anywhere    → 100% square UI, zero tolerance. Remove any
--                               rounded corners immediately. The bubble, HUD
--                               panels, dropdowns, toasts, and menus are ALL
--                               square. The color picker cursor is the only
--                               exception (it is a functional drag indicator,
--                               not a UI element). Do NOT add UICorner to new
--                               widgets; do NOT use it on buttons, frames, or
--                               popups. Breaking this rule will be reverted.
--  7. Scoping (tool state)    → ct / br / dm / sv and their helpers
--                               (SyncZone, Handles, SelectionBox, ZonePart,
--                               Menu) MUST use bare (non-local) assignment if
--                               referenced from outside their do-block. Local
--                               sv inside a do-block caused the Save crash
--                               ("attempt to index nil with 'origin'") because
--                               _ctoolGetZone could not see it. Always check
--                               definition order AND scope before adding state.
--  Rules 1-5 cause nil crashes on load. Rules 6-7 cause bugs or regressions.
--
-- ── DO NOT MODIFY (TIMING / PROTOCOL CRITICAL) ───────────────
--  HANDSHAKE = "both 🤝"   server expects this exact string
--  BUILD_SETTLE = 0.18      empirically tuned; don't lower
--  BUILD_VERIFY_WAIT = 0.35 empirically tuned
